cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new algorithm for binary classification using a hypergraph representation, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The algorithm does not require structured information and uses a set of agnostic information atoms, which suggests it could also fall under the category of data mining (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the time complexity of the algorithm and its potential to provide good performances without hyperparameter tuning, which are topics commonly studied in the fields of computational intelligence and neural networks (cs.SI, cs.NE).
